definition.value: The simplest member of the class of delta-lactone that is tetrahydro-2H-pyran substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
A glucosyl hydroxycinnamic acid that is the cinnamate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of trans-sinapic acid with the anomeric hydroxy group of beta-D-glucose.
A member of the class of cinnamaldehydes that is cinnamaldehyde substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4 and a methoxy group at position 3.
An icosatrienoic acid with three bonds at positions 5, 8 and 11.
An  organochlorine compound with insecticidal activity.
A UDP-amino sugar having 2-acetamido-4-amino-2,4,6-trideoxy-D-glucose as the sugar component.
